Tweet.Text: 12/ The Takeaway: Web3 marketing should not just lead users down a funnel but involve them in a circle of growth, learning, and governance. This isn't just marketing; it's building a community-centric economy.

Tweet.HTML:
11/ Tools for Transition:
• Use DAOs for decision-making in marketing strategies.
• Implement real-time feedback platforms integrated with blockchain for transparency.
• Educational platforms that reward learning with tokens or NFTs.

Tweet.Text:
11/ Tools for Transition:
• Use DAOs for decision-making in marketing strategies.
• Implement real-time feedback platforms integrated with blockchain for transparency.
• Educational platforms that reward learning with tokens or NFTs.

Tweet.HTML: 10/ Regenerative Marketing: Inspired by regenerative economics, where every marketing action aims to give back to the system, enhancing it rather than just extracting value. Think ad campaigns where users earn tokens for engagement.

Tweet.Text: 10/ Regenerative Marketing: Inspired by regenerative economics, where every marketing action aims to give back to the system, enhancing it rather than just extracting value. Think ad campaigns where users earn tokens for engagement.

Tweet.HTML: 8/ Transparency as Marketing: Web3's ethos is transparency. Marketing moves from behind closed doors to public forums. Every update, every decision can be part of your marketing if it's transparent and involves community feedback.

Tweet.HTML: 6/ Community Incentivization: Instead of one-off transactions, reward ongoing participation. Token systems, governance rights, or even shared revenue models encourage users to stay active and contribute, creating a self-sustaining economy.

Tweet.HTML: 5/ Sustainability Over Sales: Traditional funnels aim for sales. Circular marketing in Web3 aims for sustainable growth through community involvement. It's less about selling a product and more about building an ecosystem.
